*Info: Begin of create_pushdown_eco (mem=1943.7M)

Usage: create_pushdown_eco [-help] [-gen_script_only] [-ptn_net_dir <dirName>]
                           [-ptns <ptnNameList>] { -original_dir <dirName>  | -original_tag <tagName> } { -pushdown_dir <dirName>  | -pushdown_tag <tagName> } [ -eco_object_dir <dirName>  | -eco_tag <tagName> ]

-help                            # Prints out the command usage
-eco_object_dir <dirName>        # specifies the directory in which eco objects
                                 # for each partition will be created. The eco
                                 # objects are saved in sub-directories, one
                                 # for each partition. Default:
                                 # ./eco_object_dir (string, optional)
-eco_tag <tagName>               # specfies tag name where ECO file will be
                                 # saved. Default tag name is eco_object_dir
                                 # (string, optional)
-gen_script_only                 # generates tcl command file but does not
                                 # execute it (bool, optional)
-original_dir <dirName>          # specifies the directory in which original
                                 # partition sub-directories are present
                                 # (string, optional)
-original_tag <tagName>          # specifies tag name where original partition
                                 # pnr model is present (string, optional)
-ptn_net_dir <dirName>           # specifies the directory in which net file
                                 # (i.e., nets to be DEF eco'ed) for each
                                 # partition are present (string, optional)
-ptns <ptnNameList>              # specifies the list of partition names, for
                                 # which eco's are to be created
                                 # (string, optional)
-pushdown_dir <dirName>          # specifies the directory in which push down
                                 # (say, clock tree constructed) version of
                                 # partition sub-directories are present. These
                                 # partitions will be compared with respective
                                 # original partitions, and eco's will be
                                 # generated for each of them (string, optional)
-pushdown_tag <tagName>          # specifies tag name of the pnr model in which
                                 # contains pushed  down  data (i.e clock or
                                 # feedthrough) (string, optional)